Justice Krever stated: 
This group and others began to pay more attention to Bill C-32 after regulations appeared in The Canada Gazette on July 3, proposing the rules for environmental assessments of all foods, drugs, cosmetics and medical devices produced by biotechnology. 
The government acted prematurely. 
